node.text: One of my favorite things about summer is the bounty of fresh herbs that are just outside my doorstep. Fresh herbs make any meal instantly more flavorful and beautiful. My favorite thing to do with all of that basil (aside from sprinkle it on everything) is to make pesto! Search “basil pesto” on loveandlemons.com for the recipe.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jeanine Donofrio / Love&Lemons on August 08, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: This cherry tomato pasta is a celebration of summer. Make this one when you bring home the BEST cherry tomatoes. Half of the tomatoes cook down into a light, garlicky tomato sauce, the rest of the tomatoes stay fresh and bursty. Shower it all with lots and lots of fresh basil and enjoy. ❤️(Recipe link in profile) https://www.loveandlemons.com/cherry-tomato-pasta/

node.text: If you brought eggplant home from the farmers market, make baba ganoush! It's creamy, lemony, and a little smoky. Served with crisp veggies & warm pita, it's the perfect snack. (Recipe link in profile) https://www.loveandlemons.com/baba-ganoush/

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jeanine Donofrio / Love&Lemons on August 04, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: For the easiest summer dessert - throw a few peaches on the grill! The grill intensifies the peaches’ natural sweetness, makes them extra-juicy, and infuses them with a light smoky flavor. I love to sprinkle them with chopped nuts (or granola) and serve with vanilla ice cream. 🍑 (Recipe link in profile) https://www.loveandlemons.com/grilled-peaches/

node.text:
Cold soups don't always have to be made with tomatoes... this chilled sweet corn gazpacho is one of my favorites to make when corn season is at it's peak (aka now!) 🌽💛
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
https://www.loveandlemons.com/cold-soup-recipes/

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jeanine Donofrio / Love&Lemons on August 01, 2021. May be an image of dessert and indoor.

node.text: Got a garden full of zucchini? This zucchini bread recipe is the BEST way to use it! It's moist, tender, deliciously spiced, and super easy to make. The chocolate chips are optional, but I happen to love the combo of chocolate and zucchini. These loaves freeze well, so I always like to make a few extra. 💚 (Recipe link in profile) https://www.loveandlemons.com/zucchini-bread/

node.text:
Can a snack board count as dinner? Umm…yes, please! Lately, we’ve been celebrating summer by sharing bountiful cheese boards like this one with family and friends. I made this platter with a gorgeous haul of summer fruits, cheeses, and spreads from Whole Foods Market. With all these yummy treats, @wholefoods is here to help you make the most of the summer season, rain or shine. (#sponsored)

Every weekend through August 9, Whole Foods Market is going to monitor the weather with the @weatherchannel's @stephanieabrams. If it rains in 50% of the continental U.S., @wholefoods will make an announcement on Monday at 12 p.m. ET and give away a limited number of free Rainy-Day Redo packages filled with summer essentials. Click the link in bio for more details and to claim your Rainy-Day Redo package if a rain call is made (limited availability). #WFMRainyDayRedo

No Purch. Nec. Open to legal res of 50 US/DC, 18+only. Valid 6/21 –8/9/21. Void where prohibited Msg&data rates may apple. While supplies last.

Here’s what I included on my summer platter:

Cabot Catamount Cheddar
Mitica Wickedly Woolly sheep’s milk cheese with chervil
Rogue Creamery Organic Enraptured Blanc 
Dalmatia Organic Sour Cherry Spread
Rustic Bakery Black Sesame Organic Flatbread
Nectarines
Strawberries
Cherries
365 Brand Almonds
365 Brand Kalamata and Green Olives
Roasted 365 Brand Chickpeas

https://bit.ly/3zqIUAm

node.text: When it’s too hot to turn the oven on, make peanut butter no-bake cookies! I’ve been hooked on these chewy little cookies all week. They’re a sweet afternoon snack or an easy grab-and-go breakfast treat. 🍪(Recipe link in profile) https://www.loveandlemons.com/peanut-butter-no-bake-cookies/

node.text: Peach crisp is the first thing I make every year once peaches come into season and it's quite possibly my favorite dessert of all time. I can't get enough of that crisp nutty, oat-y topping on top of sweet, juicy peaches. 🍑 (Recipe link in profile) https://www.loveandlemons.com/peach-crisp/

node.text: If you're tired of regular coleslaw, try broccoli slaw! This creamy, colorful slaw makes a great veggie side or a perfect packable picnic salad. My favorite part about the recipe is that it uses every part of the broccoli - stalk and all! (Recipe link in profile) https://www.loveandlemons.com/broccoli-slaw-recipe/

node.text: It’s so easy to buy tomatillo salsa in a jar, but it’s SO much better when you make it fresh yourself. This is my go-to green salsa recipe. It’s fresh, it’s tangy, and a little bit spicy. Find the full recipe by searching Tomatillo Salsa on loveandlemons.com. 💚

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jeanine Donofrio / Love&Lemons on July 24, 2021. May be an image of food, drink and indoor.

node.text: There's no better beverage for summer entertaining than sangria! While I typically opt for white or rose sangria, I've been hooked on this red wine recipe with oranges, apples, and orange liquor. The perfect drink for a backyard happy hour. ❤️(Link in profile) https://www.loveandlemons.com/sangria-recipe/
